<b>DRIVER / MESSENGER / ARMED SERVICE TECHNICIAN - OPEN POSITION <br>
<br>
 Loomis seeks highly qualified individuals to join our team and become a fully functional Armored Services Technician (AST). These positions are sometimes referred to as driver/guard or messenger/guard. Check out this amazing opportunity as this could be for you!<br>
<br>
Complete an online application today at <a href="https://www.work4loomis.com" rel="nofollow">https://www.work4loomis.com</a></b><br>
<br>
Armored Service Technicians work as a team on a designated route. You will be responsible for the safe and timely delivery of cash and coin to Loomis customers, as well as the loading and balancing of ATM machines along your route. If you enjoy meeting customers and the freedom of working outside an office while wearing the uniform of one of the most respected companies in the field, this may be the opportunity for you. <br>
<br>
You will receive classroom and on-the-job training with an experienced Armored Service Technician. We believe that our people make Loomis a great company. Loomis teammates are constantly encouraged in personal development and are updated on the newest safety and security training. Our training is second to none in the industry. <br>
<br>
<b>Loomis offers a comprehensive benefits package that includes Automatic 401K Plan with company match for all employees and a selection of benefits covering Medical, Dental, Vision, Long Term Disability, Health Savings Accounts, Flexible Spending Accounts, Life Insurance, and AD&amp;D plans for the employee and their dependents.<br>
<br>Expect a stable work schedule and income every week with overtime hours and if necessary, double-time hours available. Full-time employees also have the availability of vacation pay, sick pay, jury duty pay, and holiday pay when applicable. Classroom and hands-on paid training is provided upon hire from our highly qualified instructors. Our brand new facility has the most up-to-date equipment and we offer competitive wages with multiple career opportunities of advancement worldwide.</b><br><br>
We are looking for applicants who are at least 21 years of age, have a current driver's license and a good driving record, show steady employment history and can pass a comprehensive background check that includes criminal history check, credit check and in some states a pre-employment polygraph. This position requires that you pass a Department of Transportation screening and be issued a DOT Medical Certification. A CDL license is not required to be considered.<br>
<br>
The Armored Service Technician job duties require the following physical abilities: <br>
 - Carry a minimum of 50 pounds by hand up to several hundred yards by cart <br>
 - Loading/unloading cargo consisting of multiple bags and boxes of coin <br>
 - Verbally communicate with customers <br>
 - Record information on forms and reports. <br>
<br>
We have openings for applicants for the following work schedules: <br>
 - Monday thru Saturday <br>
 - Starting time may vary between 5:00AM to 7:00AM <br>
 - Average hours per day may vary between 8 hours to 12 hours <br>
<br>
Loomis is an equal opportunity employer and a Drug Free Workplace. EOE M/F/V/D<br>
<br>
 EOE AA M/F/Vet/Disability <br>
"Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regards to their race, color, religion, national origin, sex, protected veteran status or disability"<br>
<br>
<b>TO APPLY: Complete an online application today at <a href="https://www.work4loomis.com" rel="nofollow">https://www.work4loomis.com</a></b>    </section>

